{Syntax:}\par altitude(point1, point2, point3)\par
\par Given three non-collinear points, draws the altitude of the triangle defined by the three points that passes through the first point. The triangle does not have to be drawn.\par
{\par Example:}\par altitude(A, B, C) draws a line passing through point A that is perpendicular to BC.\par }